FBIS3-11969 "drlat060_h_94002" FBIS-LAT-94-060 Document Type:Daily Report 23 Mar 1994 Honduras Army Chief Opposes Voluntary Military Proposal PA2803045294 Tegucigalpa Telesistema Hondureno Television Network in Spanish 0130 GMT 23 Mar 94 PA2803045294 Tegucigalpa Telesistema Hondureno Television Network Language: Spanish Article Type:BFN [Report by Hector Ordonez from the "This Very Day" newscast] [Text] Ironically, Armed Forces Commander Luis Alonso Discua has voiced opposition to President Carlos Roberto Reina's proposal to convert our military service into a voluntary one. Discua Elvir said the term voluntary can only be used to refer to going to the movies. The military commander also talked about the Armed Forces' ability to assist the public prosecutor in locating missing people. [passage indistinct] Referring to the Armed Forces' budget, he noted it had been significantly reduced and now amounts to approximately $33 million. Asked about Honduran Ondina Cea, who fled Iran because her father-in-law kept her in captivity, and the possibility of Iranian terrorists in Honduras, the officer said he did not have information on these matters. [Begin recording] [Unidentified reporter] Today, the Honduran's lawyer [words indistinct] charged there could be Iranian terrorists here. [Discua] Yes, as I have already told you, I do not have any information on this. You have caught me a bit off guard. I did not get any information on this when I arrived. We will take the necessary measures once we have the appropriate information. [end recording]
